OL,4,Cas she slept jailed for murder
OL,6,FSentencing her, the judge Timothy
OL,7,FSpencer KC said: "She must have woken
OL,8,Fto find her bed on fire. Flames,
OL,9,Fsmoke, an inferno. And she, unable to
OL,10,Fhear, confused, terrified. This was
OL,11,Fhell."
OL,13,FThe court heard Vamplew, who received
OL,14,Fcarer's allowance for looking after
OL,15,Fher mother-in-law and had access to
OL,16,Fher bank account, had drained it of
OL,17,Falmost #27,000 in the weeks leading up
OL,18,Fto the murder.
